--------------------------- SESSION 02: "THE ROOT'S HEART" ---------
NARRATIVE SUMMARY:
Grekel faced the Altar of Silence, offering "the living in him" to give voice to the voiceless—an act that transformed the basin and stabilized the Soul-Seed. Brother Thistle was restored, and they descended to the Iron Root. At the threshold, Grekel held off Dread-Hooves in a desperate rearguard action while Thistle entered alone. Confronted by Commander Varith, Grekel chose to enter the Root rather than flee. Inside, he found Thistle transformed—roots beneath skin, leaves in hair, the thousand voices of the Seed layered beneath his own. Thistle confessed he had known the Seed would consume him but had hidden the truth. He offered Grekel a choice: leave and forget, or stay and help him hold. Grekel chose to return to the world as a witness, carrying a living piece of the Root—a leaf-mark beneath his skin—and a charge from Varith to warn the valley of the Sleeper below.

REWARDS:
- XP: +600 (Total: 900)

FACTION ACTIVITY:
- Iron Crown: Commander Varith released Grekel; Dread-Hooves withdrawn to perimeter; Lumen-Gates on high alert. Varith preparing public revelation.
- Circle of Ash: Detected Seed planting; identified Grekel as Root-Touched; deploying hunters; accelerating excavation toward Root's foundation.
- The Sleeper: Stirred at Seed's planting; aware of "discordance" (Grekel); will begin reaching out through visions.

