--------------------------- SESSION 03: "ANCHOR DISRUPTION" --------
NARRATIVE SUMMARY:
Grekel and companions tracked the Circle of Ash scouts through hamlets and farmlands, avoiding Iron Crown patrols. Using stealth, observation, and the help of Seren, they intercepted multiple cultist groups attempting to plant ritual stakes, disrupting the Circle's anchor network. Four prisoners were captured, and four ritual stakes were recovered: two previously intact, one unpowered, and one newly cleared from the Watchtower site. Grekel studied and removed the ashes and runes, preventing the stakes from fully activating and temporarily weakening the Sleeper's network. Loot including coins, ritual components, and a dagger etched with runes was recovered. The party now has partial knowledge of the anchor network and the location of two remaining nodes (Old Ossuary Hill, River Shrine ruins), while the Circle is aware of the disruption and will likely respond.

REWARDS:
- XP: +800 (Total: 1700)

FACTION ACTIVITY:
- Iron Crown: Dread-Hooves remain on perimeter; patrols continue; unaware of this skirmish.
- Circle of Ash: Lost multiple cultists; anchor network partially disrupted; leader incapacitated. Will accelerate efforts and hunt Grekel.

