=== SESSION PATCH NOTES [SESSION 04 — "THE OSSUARY FALLS"] ===

NARRATIVE_SUMMARY:
Grekel, Seren, and the freed prisoner Mirren rode to the Iron Crown garrison, where Lieutenant Kael demanded proof of the anchor network threat. Grekel negotiated Mirren's release into his custody and shared intelligence from the captured cultists. Kael agreed to coordinate a simultaneous strike: Crown forces on the River Shrine, Grekel's party on the Ossuary Hill. At the Ossuary, Aykiyeer created a diversion while Grekel severed the southern anchor stake with the runed dagger, collapsing the ritual lattice. The mage Torven was disrupted by Eldritch Blast; the dead rose in response to the collapsing resonance. The party escaped and signaled the Crown. Varith's forces successfully destroyed the River Shrine anchor. The Sleeper's network is broken. The valley is saved—for now.

